Our examination of hematopoietic <termsem="SO:0000704"> gene </term> expression , apoptosis , and marrow histology in mon <termsem="SO:0001059"> <termsem="independent_continuant"> mutants </term> </term> demonstrates that early erythroid progenitors are formed in homozygous <termsem="SO:0001059"> <termsem="independent_continuant"> mutants </term> </term> , but they fail to properly differentiate and instead undergo programmed cell death ( see Figure 1 ) .
